---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = (href: string) => base + href;
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Use — Recursio"
  description="The basic rules for using Recursio, including AI-assisted features, accounts, subscriptions, and acceptable use."
  path="/terms"
>
  <article class="card legal">
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <p>Using Recursio means the user agrees to these Terms.</p>

    <h2>2. About Recursio</h2>
    <p>Recursio provides vocabulary, grammar, recall, writing, and AI-assisted language-learning tools.</p>

    <h2>3. Accounts</h2>
    <p>
      Users may need to sign in with Apple or Google to save progress, use subscriptions, and sync learning data.
    </p>

    <h2>4. User Responsibility</h2>
    <p>
      Users are responsible for the text they submit and must not submit unlawful, harmful, abusive, or sensitive personal content.
    </p>

    <h2>5. AI-Assisted Features</h2>
    <p>AI features may generate corrections, explanations, practice prompts, and conversation responses.</p>
    <p>AI output may be incomplete or inaccurate.</p>
    <p>
      Recursio is not a substitute for a human teacher, professional translator, or official language certification.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Subscriptions</h2>
    <p>Recursio offers optional paid plans such as SMART and PRO.</p>
    <p>
      Subscription terms are described on the <a href={url('/subscription-terms')}>Subscription Terms</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Acceptable Use</h2>
    <p>Users must not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>misuse the app</li>
      <li>attempt to reverse engineer or disrupt the service</li>
      <li>use the app for illegal purposes</li>
      <li>abuse AI features</li>
      <li>submit content that violates others’ rights</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>
      The app, design, text, software, and brand are owned by Recursio or its owner/licensors. Users keep responsibility for their own submitted learning content.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Availability and Changes</h2>
    <p>
      Features may change over time. Recursio may add, remove, or modify features, including free and paid features.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Termination</h2>
    <p>Access may be limited or terminated if the user violates these Terms.</p>

    <h2>11. Disclaimers</h2>
    <p>Recursio is provided “as is” and does not guarantee specific learning outcomes.</p>

    <h2>12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the extent permitted by law, Recursio is not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential losses, lost learning outcomes, or decisions made based on AI feedback. Users are responsible for how they apply information learned through the app.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms can be sent to <a href="mailto:support@recursio.app">support@recursio.app</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="accent-surface">
      <strong>Note:</strong> This document is a draft and should be reviewed by qualified legal counsel before publication. Legal entity details are placeholders.
    </div>
  </article>
</LegalLayout>
